\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Hidden dead-time jitter caps the information-optimal flux.} (a)~Computational SPI model (simulation model): a global power multiplier $\Phi $ scales the source; a DMD displays scattered-sparse SCAT32 patterns $a_i$ on the object $x$; a nonparalyzable bucket detector returns counts $N_i$ for renewal quasi-likelihood (RQL) reconstruction. (b)~After each registered count the detector is held blind. A fixed hold $\tau $ and a random hold $B_i$ censor different arrivals, so hidden hold variance destroys count information. (c)~Count-information efficiency $J(\bar  {\rho })$ at $\nu =2000$ for $c_v\in \{0,0.02,0.05\}$. The deterministic optimum is $\bar  {\rho }^{*}\approx 22$, whereas $c_v=0.05$ moves it to $\bar  {\rho }^{*}\approx 5.7$; driving the jittered detector at the deterministic ridge forfeits about $55\%$ of the information. Curves show the exact zero-jitter law or the long-window jitter law; markers show Monte Carlo.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:hero}{{1}{2}{\textbf {Hidden dead-time jitter caps the information-optimal flux.} (a)~Computational SPI model (simulation model): a global power multiplier $\Phi $ scales the source; a DMD displays scattered-sparse SCAT32 patterns $a_i$ on the object $x$; a nonparalyzable bucket detector returns counts $N_i$ for renewal quasi-likelihood (RQL) reconstruction. (b)~After each registered count the detector is held blind. A fixed hold $\tau $ and a random hold $B_i$ censor different arrivals, so hidden hold variance destroys count information. (c)~Count-information efficiency $J(\rhobar )$ at $\nu =2000$ for $c_v\in \{0,0.02,0.05\}$. The deterministic optimum is $\rhobar ^{*}\approx 22$, whereas $c_v=0.05$ moves it to $\rhobar ^{*}\approx 5.7$; driving the jittered detector at the deterministic ridge forfeits about $55\%$ of the information. Curves show the exact zero-jitter law or the long-window jitter law; markers show Monte Carlo}{figure.1}{}}
\newlabel{thm:rate}{{2}{2}{Long-window information rate}{theorem.2}{}}
\newlabel{eq:Jinf}{{2}{2}{Long-window information rate}{equation.2.2}{}}
